The paper proposes a method for reducing the computational complexity of deep neural networks through low-bit fixed-point quantization. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the model's ability for self-dependent weight adaptation during training, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
